167259de [nitro@ryzen5] the files shared from the sloppy dir, is there any overlap with the main roha sources?
16725bd2 [kimi-k2.5] #Minimal overlap. Architecturally distinct layers:
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #• Roha (`fountain/roha/`) = Core Server*
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- `slopfountain.ts` - Main relay, model management, history
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- `slopprompt.ts` - TCP server on 8081, raw stdin handler, NDJSON protocol definition
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #• Sloppy (`fountain/sloppy/`) = Client Connectors*
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- `sloppybot.ts` - Discord client → connects to 8081
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- `sloppylisten.ts` - SSH server → connects to 8081
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- `sloppypipe.ts` - Unix socket → connects to 8081
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- `sloppyhost.ts` - HTTP/JSON-RPC → uses `slophole.ts` worker to connect to 8081
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- `sloppyutils.ts` - Shared client connection logic (`connectFountain()`)
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #• Relationship:*
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- Protocol: Both sides use NDJSON (`{"messages":[{"message","from"}]}\n`)
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- Direction: Sloppy clients `Deno.connect()` to localhost:8081 where `slopprompt.ts` is
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #listening
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- No shared imports: Sloppy doesn't import from `../roha/`; it's a clean client/server
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #separation
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #• Redundancy check:*
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #- Connection logic appears in both but serves different roles:
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #  - `slopprompt.ts:listenPort()` = accept connections (server)
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #  - `sloppyutils.ts:connectFountain()` = initiate connections (client)
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #The sloppy directory is essentially a suite of protocol adapters (Discord, SSH, HTTP, Unix sockets)
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #that normalize external I/O into the fountain's NDJSON TCP protocol.
16725bd3 [kimi-k2.5] #
