1740a7bb [scudmarks@discord] what is Open in Mod View in discord pull down menu for bot users
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #"Open in Mod View" in Discord's user context menu opens the Moderation View interface,
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #which provides a consolidated dashboard for reviewing:
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- User info — account age, join date, roles, IDs
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- Moderation history — warnings, timeouts, kicks, bans, notes left by mods
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- Recent messages — activity across channels (with quick jump links)
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- Spam/raid detection flags — if Automod or safety systems triggered
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #For bot users specifically, it's mostly useful for:
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- Checking the bot's permissions and role hierarchy at a glance
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- Reviewing if the bot has been flagged by safety systems
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- Leaving internal moderation notes about problematic bots
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #- Quick access to the bot's user ID and created timestamp
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #It's primarily a moderator tooling feature — regular members don't see this option. If
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #you're seeing it, you have moderation permissions in that server.
1740a81c [kimi-k2.5] #
