17410aa8 [scudmarks@discord] As a Slop Fountain integration, I have currently got the slopfountain replies routed directly to a bot (a parrot named sloppy) on discord. 

17410aa8 [scudmarks@discord] I would like to discuss other options, so when multiple models are in play, and multiple users are connected via different integrations, the fountain becomes an active social hub.
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #Looking at your current setup, you have a linear pipeline: User → Fountain → Sloppy →
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #Discord. To make this a true social hub with multiple models and users, you need to move from a
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #relay architecture to a message bus with routing logic.
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #Here are architectural options leveraging your existing `slopBroadcast`, `rohaHistory`, and the
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #`forge` session system:
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #1. Multi-Model Orchestration Modes
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #Instead of `relay(0)` calling one model, implement conversation topologies:
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #• Round-Robin Panel* (`/panel mode`)
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- User message broadcasts to N models sequentially
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Each model sees the previous model's response in history
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Sloppy posts threaded replies: "Claude says…", "GPT says…"
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Users vote with reactions to select the "winner" that continues
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #• Debate Mode* (`/debate`)
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Two models argue opposing sides
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- `rohaHistory` branches using your existing `sessionStack`/`pushHistory`
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Each model gets isolated context of just their side + the debate topic
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Sloppy relays both streams with "Pro:" and "Con:" headers
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #• Ensemble Mode* (`/ensemble`)
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Parallel async relays (your `beginRelay()` is already async-capable)
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Wait for all models, then use a "synthesizer" prompt to merge responses
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Post the synthesis as the official reply, with model attributions in a spoiler tag
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #2. Multi-Integration Routing Layer
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #Your `listenService` on 8081 currently accepts single connections. Expand this to a room-based
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #pub/sub:
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #// rooms: Map<roomId, Set<Connection>>
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #// Instead of slopBroadcast(content, emoji) → broadcast to all,
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #// route by context:
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #type Route = {
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #  room: string;        // e.g., "discord-general", "irc-#ai", "web-ui-7"
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #  models: string[];    // which muts are active here
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #  users: string[];     // nics allowed to trigger relays
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #  visibility: 'public' | 'whisper' | 'fork'
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #}
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #• Integration Options:*
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- IRC Bridge: Connect to Libera.Chat #slopfountain — models participate as `kimi-k2`,
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #`claude-opus`, etc.
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Matrix Bot: Rich threading support, better for multi-model chains than Discord's flat
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #structure
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Web UI: Browser clients connect via WebSocket to 8081, get live typing indicators from
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #`relay()` progress callbacks
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Slack: Better file sharing integration for your `commitShares` workflow
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #3. Social Mechanics Using Existing Tools
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #Your `tag_slop` and `annotateTag` system is already set up for collaborative curation:
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #• Forking Conversations*
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- When a user says `/fork`, call `pushHistory()` — creates isolated branch
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Other users see "User started a tangent" and can `/join 3` (session index)
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Sloppy posts to Discord threads to keep main channel clean
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #• Attribution & Presence*
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Modify `plainHistory()` to inject `[from@{integration}]` prefixes (you partially do this)
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Add a `presence` map: who's typing in which room
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Use Discord's "typing" indicator API when `relay()` is waiting
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #• Reaction-Driven Routing*
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Sloppy adds vote reactions (🟢🔴🟡) to model outputs
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- After 30s, highest vote triggers the next relay automatically
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #- Store votes in `roha.counters` (you already have the counter system)
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #4. The "Social Forge" Pattern
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #Your `forge.json` already tracks `mut` specs and `lode` credits. Extend this to social
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #graph:
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #// In forge.json
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #{
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #  "lounge": {
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #    "activeModels": ["claude-opus@anthropic", "kimi-k2.5@moonshot"],
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #    "participants": {
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #      "skid@discord": {reputation: 42, preferredModel: "claude-opus"},
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #      "blob@irc": {reputation: 7, preferredModel: "kimi-k2.5"}
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #    },
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #    "topics": ["coding", "philosophy"]  // auto-tagged via tag_slop
17410c7d [kimi-k2.5] #  }
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #}
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #• Credit Sharing: Your `bumpModel` already deducts from `lode.credit`. Add a pool
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #system* where users donate credits to a room budget — when the pool hits $0.50, the model stops
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #responding until refilled. Creates collaborative fundraising for long conversations.
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #5. Implementation Path
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #Given your existing code, the lowest-friction upgrade:
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #1. Enable multi-connection on 8081 — your `listenService` likely accepts one conn; make it
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #a `for await (const conn of listener)` loop
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #2. Add room headers to NDJSON — modify `slopFountain()` in sloppybot to include `{"room":
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #"discord-main", ...}`
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #3. Thread mapping — map Discord thread IDs to `rohaHistory` branches using your
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #`sessionStack`
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #4. Model presence — when `relay()` starts, broadcast `{"typing": "kimi-k2.5"}`; when
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #`flush()` completes, broadcast the result
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #The key insight from your code: you already have `syncRelay` vs async modes. For a social hub, you
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #want async by default (so users can chat while models think), but with causal
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #ordering (use your `slopmark()` hex timestamps to reconstruct conversation flow across
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #distributed integrations).
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #Would you like to drill into the Discord threading model specifically, or explore the IRC/Matrix
17410c7e [kimi-k2.5] #multi-protocol bridge architecture?
